        purposeDesc: 'Public administration research informs how governments and public organizations function, how policies are implemented, and how public services are delivered. Papers must establish the public interest significance of the research question, ground the study in theories of bureaucracy, governance, or public management, and produce findings relevant to practitioners in government agencies, nonprofit organizations, or international institutions. A clear structure helps diverse readers follow the argument from policy problem to evidence-based recommendation.',
