          'Comparative Case Studies: Selects cases (countries, agencies, programs) based on theoretical criteria (most similar, most different, deviant cases) to develop or test propositions about governance and policy.',
          'Survey Research: Designs and administers surveys to public employees, citizens, or stakeholders to measure perceptions of organizational culture, public service motivation, trust in government, or service satisfaction.',
