        purposeDesc: 'The journal landscape in literature and linguistics is organized by national tradition, period, genre, theoretical orientation, and linguistic sub-field. Unlike the social sciences, where a few top-tier journals dominate, literary studies values publication in specialized journals that reach expert communities. Citation style is a crucial marker of disciplinary identity: MLA is standard in literary studies, Chicago (notes-bibliography) in history and interdisciplinary humanities, and journal-specific formats in linguistics.',
        elements: 'Important Journals and Resources',
